    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">Faster regexs using \%(query\) notation (equiv to perl's (?:query) notation) and other extremely minor tweaks like 'exists' no longer accepting functions.&nbsp;&nbsp;I haven't touched this since 5/4/9, as reflected in internal release date, but I (wrongly) figured I'd tweak it more before another release.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's pretty much done now, so I don't expect more releases.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are two remaining TODO items:&nbsp;&nbsp;one for reorganization (code cleanup) which is mostly unnecessary, and one assuming there is more perl highlighting to disable/tweak (though I haven't seen any evidence recently).&nbsp;&nbsp;One more TODO is the recognition of regexs using alternate bounding characters like apostrophe instead of slash.</td>
</tr>
